{"_id":"Vy8vl2mJyaeZ9s6W","name":"Dark Ego - I Will Have My Satisfaction","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am a man of the world and nothing can really surprise me anymore. I never question myself. After all, I’m the best at what I do.<h3>Dark Ego</h3>When you choose an opponent, there is no escape for them. Once per Scene, you can take an additional action against the target of your challenge (even if you had already acted during this Exchange) to anticipate their move and stop their action with yours. If an opponent inflicts a Wound on you, you savor the taste of the challenge and receive 1 Additional Success at each Check against them for the rest of the Scenario.","notes":"James the Swordsman - bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 4.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"You challenge an enemy or otherwise make clear who and how skilled you are."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241691,"modifiedTime":1783973241691,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"VRrgMVpuB99iKBAa","name":"Dark Ego - The Big Bad Wolf","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am fiercer and more powerful than any human and my fangs can pierce even metal. My proud wolf spirit is everything to me.<h3>Dark Ego</h3>You are hardened by a lifetime in the great mountains and your skill is matched only by your courage. When you unleash your rage, create a Descriptor for it that includes at least one of these words: Strong, Fierce, Unstoppable. You can employ the strength of three men, gnaw through stone as easily as flesh, or break down any barrier. When you act using this special Descriptor for Position Checks, you get 1 Additional Success. Once per Scene, you can unleash your rage and receive 3 Additional Successes instead of 1.","notes":"Garou the Old Wolf - bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 6.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"You assume the form of a Wolf or reveal yourself for what you really are, scaring off weak humans."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241691,"modifiedTime":1783973241691,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"59gVW5SM6kTbuaG0","name":"Dark Ego - The Power of Music","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>As an artist I have traveled to many places and I know many myths and legends. I’m hungry for knowledge and I’m fascinated by everything I don’t know.<h3>Dark Ego</h3>Once per Scene, you can make a sound that can be heard by whomever you wish, even from a great distance. Everyone who hears it suffers 1 Wound, fragile objects break, and frightened animals flee. Alternatively, you can play a gentle melody and the wind itself will obey you, carrying your message to whomever you wish, wherever they are. When using The Power of Music, you can also activate a Soul Music effect on one or more targets of your choice.","notes":"The Astonishing Pied Piper Without a Name - bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 8.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Demonstrate your art to its fullest extent, with a show that cannot be ignored."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241691,"modifiedTime":1783973241691,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"1BSPSTCB2YO9EqEq","name":"Dark Ego - The Evil Witch","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>Like any respectable sorceress, I carry my trusty bag full of herbs, poisons, and all kinds of magic tools. My childlike appearance is often useful, but sometimes it leads others to underestimate me. I hate that.<h3>Dark Ego</h3>Receive 1 Additional Success on any Check when you use one of your spells, either through the Magic Gift or by inserting it into your narrative through the Descriptors. Moreover, you can unleash your evil aura to gain one or more of the following effects:\n1. Animals and ordinary people are tormented by your presence and will flee in terror.\n2. You gain 1 Additional Success if you use your magic to punish someone for breaking a promise or agreement you made earlier.\n3. In the area around you, you can summon daylight or darkness.","notes":"Baba yaga The Child Witch - bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 10.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Scare ordinary people or dispense punishment through your magic."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241691,"modifiedTime":1783973241691,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"lxVBw4oloH2FBLs4","name":"Dark Ego - As I Want!","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I have an enviable charm and love to dress up to fit the role I have chosen. Even when I try to restrain myself, I never go unnoticed.<h3>Dark Ego</h3>You know that your way is the only right way to do things. During the Scene, as an additional action, you can choose another character who will be issued a command. In the case of an ally, if they do exactly what you tell them, they will receive 1 Additional Success to their action or increase their Opposition Level by 1. If you give a peremptory order to ensnare an enemy, they will lower their Opposition Level by 1 or, if you’ve already seen it in action, you can prevent them from using one of their Gifts. Once per Scene, you can shout, drawing everyone’s attention to you. For a few moments, they will pause to listen to what you have to say.","notes":"Regina The Thief Of Hearts - bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 12.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Take control of a situation and impose your decisions by dramatically drawing attention to yourself."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241691,"modifiedTime":1783973241691,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"okLhO5Pi59LmOb7O","name":"Dark Ego - If you don’t Stop, I’ll Call the Bogeyman!","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>My presence intimidates people, touching the fear that dwells deep in their hearts. The presence of children and their innocent way of looking at the world makes me uneasy.<h3>Dark Ego</h3>You are like a sinuous shadow that can reach anywhere. During a Scene, you can arrive at a location by covering any distance and overcoming any obstacle if one of your allies or an NPC calls your name. When you manifest your true nature, everyone who witnesses it will be frightened and will not act against you unless you threaten them first. The Storyteller may ask you for a Position Check to frighten particularly powerful characters. Receive 1 Additional Success on all Defense Checks you make against the actions of someone who is now fearful.","notes":"Babai the Judge - bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 14.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Enter or leave a shadow by manifesting your true nature and scaring someone."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241692,"modifiedTime":1783973241692,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"2xU4KRIDjHUv5JaW","name":"Dark Ego - Soft and Succulent Flesh","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I love human flesh and can gain insight about people just looking at them. I am helplessly attracted to those who have a particular physical trait that stimulates my appetite, such as a good smell or velvety skin.<h3>Dark Ego</h3>The truth is that you crave human flesh, especially when raw and taken from evil people. When you inflict a Wound through violent action on someone you deem evil, and if you reach an Outcome with an Increment, you may inflict 1 additional Wound. Once per Scene when you consume human flesh, you recover 1 Wound and the Storyteller will reveal some memories of the victim, giving you contextualized information about what you are looking for.","notes":"The Woman from the Woods - bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 16.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Blatantly manifest your desire to devour human flesh, regardless of the consequences."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241692,"modifiedTime":1783973241692,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"Ke4XIrSMRgQiHycG","name":"Dark Ego - The Immortal","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>My body is but a tool which I can manipulate at will, far beyond common human limits. In spite of my old and emaciated appearance, I feel neither fatigue nor pain. With matters of the flesh no longer of concern, I value beautiful things and works of art above anything else.<h3>Dark Ego</h3>When you suffer 1 Wound, you can immediately spend 1 Soma to remain conscious, allowing you to suffer many Wounds without dying. You are in full control of your body, even parts that have been cut off. You can see through a torn eye or continue to use your severed hand. At the end of the Scene in which you activated your Dark Ego, you recover all Wounds suffered except the first one. Your body regenerates and severed parts reattach in a horrific spectacle.","notes":"TheImmortal - bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 18.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Use your indifference to pain or death to your advantage, revealing your true nature for anyone to see."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241692,"modifiedTime":1783973241692,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"n7nOsNsHPxeE04dH","name":"Dark Ego - Treasures of the Sea","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I have a massive collection of magical relics and treasures. I am very stingy with my collection and constantly seeking to add to my wealth so I can redeem my freedom.<h3>Dark Ego</h3>At the beginning of the Scenario, you receive 2 Treasure Tokens. When you show off your Treasures, spend 1 Treasure Token and 1 Soma, and create a Descriptor that represents it such as Wolf-Slaying Dagger or Lens of Truth. Receive 1 Additional Success for any Check in which your Treasure may be helpful. Alternatively, spend 1 Token to draw a Potion from your pouch to give to someone. Create a Descriptor to represent its magical effect such as Seeing in the dark or Extraordinary strength. Whoever drinks it will be granted the Descriptor you created for 1 Scene, plus 1 Additional Success on the first action in which they use the advantage given by the potion. When you obtain a new treasure or close a favorable deal, you receive 1 Treasure Token.","notes":"Marina the Sea Explorer - bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 20.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Turn a request for help or a conversation into a negotiation, making it clear how amazing your treasures are."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241692,"modifiedTime":1783973241692,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"YVpBR3Xwp7hPnaPN","name":"Dark Ego - The Demon Revealed","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>The demon in me grants me its power, allowing me to act with savage strength and speed. It is not easy to contain this ferocity and, often, I end up hurting or destroying things I did not wish to.<h3>Dark Ego</h3>While generally retaining control, every now and then you have to allow the demon to manifest and unleash its anger. Create a Descriptor that represents your demonic form and that includes at least one of these words: Monstrous, Fierce, Beastly. Your physical abilities go far beyond those of a mere mortal, but you will behave like a devil, enjoying the evil and fear you inspire. When you act using this special Descriptor, you gain 1 Additional Success. You can spend 1 Devil Token to inflict 1 additional Wound or to spend as Soma for a Check. Once per Scenario, the Storyteller can spend 1 Devil Token to activate this Gift against your will.","notes":"Niklaus von Krampus - bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 22.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Give free rein to your demonic side or listen to the sound of bells or cowbells for at least one minute."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241692,"modifiedTime":1783973241692,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"WMWOfghoddbhq818","name":"Dark Ego - The Saint","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am a saint in the eyes of ordinary people and no door remains closed for me. My word is that of the Church itself. What I say is not to be questioned.<h3>Dark Ego</h3>When you channel sacred divine power, everyone bows their heads. Ordinary people will show you reverence, while weaker enemy NPCs (at the Storyteller’s discretion) won’t target you unless you’re the only available option, nor will they try to get in your way. In your presence, anyone possessing powers linked to the supernatural lowers their Opposition Level by 1. Your holy aura emits an intense light that can illuminate the whole area around you at your will.","notes":"George the Holy Dragon Slayer - bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 24.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Invoke holy divine power by reproaching all sinners and providing an example of purity and righteousness."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241692,"modifiedTime":1783973241692,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"KdPxC6sGdnW8CsmL","name":"Dark Ego - Descendant of the Awakening of the Void and the Emptiness","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>My essence is magical, and this makes me resistant to enchantments that might snare stupid humans. My spiritual presence is imposing, and I struggle to hide what I am, especially in the eyes of those accustomed to magic.<h3>Dark Ego</h3>When you release your true power, your body emits a divine light and no one can stop you. Take 1 Wound to get 2 Additional Successes to any physical Checks you have to perform. For the rest of the Scene spells have little effect on you and you get 2 Additional Successes to any Defense Check you make to protect yourself from arcane effects. When you deal a hit to someone, you can spend 1 Soma to inflict 1 additional Wound. The effects of this Gift cease if you behave in a composed and obedient manner, as your role as guardian dictates.","notes":"Sun Wukong the Amazing Monkey - bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 26.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Act with passion and strength, showing everyone the incredible power that lies within your body."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241692,"modifiedTime":1783973241692,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"oHHqcuRoKu5TfEyO","name":"Dark Ego - The Unscrupulous Assassin","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>Under the facade of a respectable man hides a skilled, unscrupulous problem-solver. I know how to kill and how to act with decisiveness. Everyone has done something they are not proud of and I can’t stand seeing the hypocrites who pretend as if they are morally superior to others.<h3>Dark Ego</h3>You may appear as a civilized gentleman, but appearances can be deceiving. When necessary, you will not hesitate to kill. If you eliminate an NPC by inflicting a final Wound, you can also immediately eliminate a second Minor NPC. When you successfully defend yourself from a violent action, you can immediately eliminate a Minor NPC in response. Either way, the target must be within range of your wrath. After inflicting 1 Wound to someone, you can move freely as an additional action, allowing you to reach your true goal without anyone preventing you from doing so.","notes":"Verdoux Bluebeard - bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 28.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Reveal your dark side by injuring someone or acting aggressively despite your outwardly calm and staid appearance."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241693,"modifiedTime":1783973241693,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"RcU9qkh6Vi8KJPAx","name":"Dark Ego - Ice-Cold","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>My body is pure ice and, because of this, I can manipulate ice as I please. However, I hate to manifest my power because it is dangerous to those around me and, as an artist, my purpose is to make people smile.<h3>Dark Ego</h3>You have control over your body temperature and, consequently, you can freeze the environment or objects in your immediate vicinity. When you manipulate ice, choose an effect by creating a Descriptor that represents it such as: Frozen Door or Aura of Frost and spend 1 Soma to manifest it for the whole Scene. As an additional effect, your frost can inflict 1 Wound on those who interact with it or make what you freeze incredibly fragile or incredibly hard. Whoever exploits the effects of frost in their favor gains 1 Additional Success for their action. Your frost has no direct effect on living things.","notes":"Yukie Onn the Traveling Artist - bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 30.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Shed your disguise as a simple artist and reveal your true, bitterly cold form or react passionately when fear and intimidation are used for selfish reasons."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241693,"modifiedTime":1783973241693,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"D0rGBEuCd9GD1pR1","name":"Dark Ego - The Fox and the Cat","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>Like it or not, we are bound by magic. We can share thoughts, each see what the other sees, and thanks to this we can work together to cheat others. Whoever is in animal form hates not being able to communicate and often annoys the other out of spite.<h3>Dark Ego</h3>You and your partner share Soma and Wounds. The human form can spend 1 Soma to use the Gift of the animal form. Once per Scene, if your partner helps you, you gain +2 Additional Successes on a Position Check.","notes":"Cunning Machiavelli the Fox and Sly Bischeri the Cat - bt-cb-foxcat-sheet-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 2.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Trick or deceive someone, taking advantage of your partner's support."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241693,"modifiedTime":1783973241693,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"CidScEy5HMRrYaXG","name":"Dark Ego - Alice of Other Worlds","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>Alice of\nOther Worlds\nAs a child I traveled to other worlds and my mind can perceive and see \nthings beyond common perception. Memories of my childhood haunt me, \nand I often get lost in visions of the past.<h3>Dark Ego</h3>As an action, you may spend \n1 Soma to try to possess the body of a person or animal that is looking into \nyour eyes. Particularly powerful individuals may require a Position Check for \nyou to succeed. Y ou can act through the body you possess and continue to use \nyour Gifts and Descriptors, but you receive an additional Descriptor created \nby the Storyteller and representing the abilities of the body you are possessing. \nThe possession ends at the end of the Scene, when the possessed body suffers 1 \nWound, or you decide to return to your body of your own volition. While you \ncontrol someone else’s body, your original body is inert and at the mercy of the \nworld. Y ou cannot possess Broken Tales or supernatural creatures. Y our mind is \nnot easy to control, so you gain 1 Additional Success for Defense Checks against \nany kind of mind control and magic.","notes":"Alice of Other Worlds - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 2.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"You notice a detail that does not match what you consider normal.\nXP\nSoma\n 5"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241693,"modifiedTime":1783973241693,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"CWDhSgU35OFKvtxf","name":"Dark Ego - Beasts in Body and Soul","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am linked to Dionysus and we share pain and perceptions. He will \nalways know where I am and vice versa. For me, that’s the most \nhumiliating part of the curse.<h3>Dark Ego</h3>When you reveal your \ntrue nature everyone is horrified. One is a beast in body, while the other \nis a beast in her soul. Y ou receive 3 Savagery Tokens that you can spend \nduring the Scene to: \n1. Inflict 1 additional Wound, if Dionysus spends an action to help you in \nthe attack. The Wound will be a strikingly bloody gash.\n2. Have a minor NPC lose their action as they are intimidated, having \nwitnessed the fury of Dionysus.\n3. If Dionysus is not present in the Scene, he can appear immediately \n(possibly tearing a new opening in the environment, demolishing any \npossible obstacle) to support you. \n4. Perform a second action in the Exchange, if Dionysus spends one of his \nto open the way for you.","notes":"Beauty and her Beast - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 4.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Unleash the feral power of Dionysus, or humiliate or betray \nsomeone, revealing your true nature."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241693,"modifiedTime":1783973241693,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"FyiPbkfPtesW9tkz","name":"Dark Ego - Pure Innocence","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3><h3>Dark Ego</h3>When you appeal to the \npurity of your heart, even the foulest spell is broken. When you \nactivate your Dark Ego during a Scene, you become immune to \nany effect of fear or mind control, and all subjects you consider evil \nlower their Opposition Level by 1 in your presence. Y ou can spend 1 \nMutation Token to give 1 Additional Success to the first action of all \nallies who admire you for who you are.","notes":"Bloodwhite - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 6.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Open your heart and appeal to the goodness of those close to \nyou, revealing who you are, or sacrifice something of yourself for others.\nXP\nSoma\n 5"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241693,"modifiedTime":1783973241693,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"RrJuN1n2cLyHMyLP","name":"Dark Ego - Soulless Puppet","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3><h3>Dark Ego</h3>Y our body is made of wood and \nso you ignore any penalty derived from dangers that would affect a living \nbeing. Y ou receive 1 Additional Success to all your Defense Checks. Y ou \ncan communicate with other puppets or toys who can tell you something \nat the Storyteller’s discretion. If you stay still, you will pass as a common \npuppet in the eyes of those who see you and you cannot be discovered \nexcept with special skills or magic.","notes":"Wound. Carlo the LivingPuppet - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 8.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Make obvious use of the wooden properties of your body to perform \nan action, or have your nose grow dramatically (i.e. when you accumulate \nthe third Lie Token), proving to everyone that you are not human."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241693,"modifiedTime":1783973241693,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"UuF4EVz4vYZqqMR5","name":"Dark Ego - Mad like a Hatter","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3><h3>Dark Ego</h3>When you give free rein to \nyour madness, reality bends itself to prove you right. Declare something \ncrazy such as That door leads to the opposite side of town, or This pair \nof glasses allows you to see ghosts and create a Descriptor. Y our madness \nmust always concern an object and its crazy use. Y ou cannot directly affect \nor interact with living beings. Suffer 1 Wound caused by the fatigue of \nturning your madness into reality. Y our madness lasts throughout the \nScene. If at least one subject is amazed by what you do with your madness, \nyou gain 1 Soma.","notes":"Hatta Carter - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 10.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Behave and talk like a crazy person, not worrying about the \nreactions of those around you."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241693,"modifiedTime":1783973241693,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"zDMwqZTnhYKSOJ1H","name":"Dark Ego - The Headless Knight","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3><h3>Dark Ego</h3>Y ou are an immortal \nvengeful spirit. When you suffer your last Wound, you dissolve into \nthin air to return at the beginning of the next Scene having recovered 2","notes":"The Knight with a Hundred Heads - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 12.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":""},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241694,"modifiedTime":1783973241694,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"ThEjMveNoiXwksj9","name":"Dark Ego - The Young Wolf","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>Iskra the\n Young\nWolf I am a wolf child and I defend myself with fangs and claws. My \nsense of smell is infallible. I’m young and I know little about the \nworld, so I am easily intimidated when I face something I don’t \nknow.<h3>Dark Ego</h3>Unleash your feral side, ready to bite anyone who opposes your pack. If you get an Outcome with an \nIncrement on a Position Check, you can spend the Increment to take an \nadditional action immediately. Y ou can also inflict 1 Wound on yourself \nto perform an additional action after your normal action. Y ou can’t \nperform more than 3 actions per Exchange. Y ou may spend 1 Soma \nto memorize the smell of a person you are interacting with. Y ou will \nalways recognize them and it will be easy for you to follow their tracks \neven after a long time.","notes":"Iskra the Young Wolf - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 14.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Give free rein to your feral side or fulfill a task for your pack with your wolf skills.\nXP\nSoma\n 6"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241694,"modifiedTime":1783973241694,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"e0c6tk9ec0MB6ays","name":"Dark Ego - Our Home","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>We are capable builders and there is no building that we cannot fortify or infiltrate. We \nare very protective of what we think is ours.<h3>Dark Ego</h3>When you arrive in a new location, you can take the \ntime to examine, alter, and repair it. Y ou may use one of the following options for each \npresent gang member.\n1. Escape route: Detail a Descriptor that represents an escape route that only you \nmay open.\n2. Trap: Detail a Descriptor that describes how your trap activates and hurts intruders. \nThose who enter the perimeter will trigger it, suffering 1 Wound. Skilled and attentive \nindividuals may require a Position Check to fall into your trap.\n3. Improvement: Create a Descriptor that represents an improvement you make to \nthe environment. Y ou get 1 Additional Success when you make use of your improvement \nduring an action.\n4. Alter: Detail a Descriptor that represents a new feature of the site that only you can \nactivate.","notes":"The Gang of three Pigs - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 16.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Take time to work on a location and make it your own."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241694,"modifiedTime":1783973241694,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"em34yFhYBydgLnEJ","name":"Dark Ego - The Supreme Fairy","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3><h3>Dark Ego</h3>Y ou can unleash your true \nfairy essence and alter reality itself. When you do this, you suffer 1 Wound \nand choose an effect:\n1. Making the Unreal a Reality: One of your illusions becomes \nreal. If necessary, the Storyteller must create an ad hoc profile.\n2. Supreme Fairy: Y ou may replicate a Gift with a magical effect you \nhave witnessed at least once during the Scenario, for the duration of the \nScene.\n3. Lady of Destiny: Y ou can change the fate of a Minor NPC by \nrewriting its Descriptor and Agenda. This may not affect particularly \npowerful NPCs or enemies, at the Storyteller’s discretion.","notes":"Morgana of the Lake - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 18.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Evoke your true potential when experiencing a strong emotion or \nwhen you find yourself in a magically charged location, and let yourself be \nflooded with power."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241694,"modifiedTime":1783973241694,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"BvaYgVaAclN2Ehf9","name":"Dark Ego - From Another World","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am a person out of her time and largely immune to those who use spells and \nmagic. I have a natural talent for fighting those who use magic. I hate witches \nand sorcerers because, despite their power, they can’t heal me.<h3>Dark Ego</h3>As a creature displaced in time, you \nare naturally resistant to magic. Y ou gain 2 Additional Successes when defending \nyourself from a danger associated with magic. When you inflict 1 Wound on a \nbeing associated with magic, you prevent them from using their powers (Gifts and \nDescriptors) during their next action. Blocking the powers of particularly powerful \nopponents and Hunters may require a Position Check. When you touch a magic or \nenchanted object, you can spend 1 Soma to temporarily interrupt its power. The \nduration of this effect is decided by the Storyteller.","notes":"OZena the Suffering - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 20.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Reveal that you’re from another time through a gesture or a word. \nAlternatively, act threatening towards a magical being."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241694,"modifiedTime":1783973241694,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"iUr6oheUUZcRr9Dq","name":"Dark Ego - One Thousand and One Nights","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>Sherazade \nthe Weaver of \nTales\nMy stories become reality. Shadows, those ubiquitous reflections of \nreality, can interact with me. A life among the shadows in my bedroom \nhas made it hard for me to bear sunlight.<h3>Dark Ego</h3>One of the \ncharacters in a story you told during the Session comes to life as a Shadow. \nCreate a Descriptor for them, ensuring it is driven to support you. The \nShadow could, for example, fly or walk on water. The Shadow thus created \nwill be at your service and will do whatever you order with an OL Medium 5 \nand 1 Wound. For each Story Token you decide to spend, you can summon \nan additional Shadow. Y our Shadows do not speak and cannot act in places \nwhere there is more light than darkness.","notes":"Sherazade the Weaver of Tales - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 22.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Manifest your affinity for the shadows or tell a dark story full of \nfear and monsters.\nXP\nSoma\n 6"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241694,"modifiedTime":1783973241694,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"SITXQaIu3RUAcHO4","name":"Dark Ego - The Sleeping Will","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I can move objects with the power of thought alone. Through this power, \nI am able to manifest my presence in the world. My real body is immobile \nand locked in eternal sleep, at the mercy of the world. I long for the \nleast caress, which would remind me of being alive.<h3>Dark Ego</h3>Y ou can use your power to \nmanipulate the objects around you. Y ou can make small items float or \nthrow them like weapons. Y ou can affect your surroundings up to 30 feet \naway. Y ou can act up to 3 times in an Exchange, manipulating the world \naround you, but you cannot act more than once against the same target. \nOnce per Scene, you can focus all 3 actions on a single large object (like a \nhouse) and manipulate it to your liking.","notes":"Talia the Sleeper - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 24.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Shed your cloak, revealing your helpless body or exposing yourself \nto others by manipulating the world around you."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241694,"modifiedTime":1783973241694,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"F72yZCjfpZmurLss","name":"Dark Ego – Solitary Ghost","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3><h3>Dark Ego</h3>When you decide to take on your ghostly \nform, you receive 1 Solitude Token and become intangible. Y ou cannot have any kind \nof physical interaction with the world (not even talking) and no one can touch you, \nexcept through magic. However, you do not become invisible to the human eye and so \nthose who see you will understand that you are a ghost. In the form of a specter, your \naffinity to fire is more intense and you gain 1 Additional Success in any action involving \nthe flames you are manipulating. In addition, you can spend 1 Soma to ignite a flame \nfrom thin air and set something on fire. The effect of this Gift lasts until you decide to \nstop it, but the Storyteller can spend 1 Solitude Token to force you to remain ethereal \nfor a few more minutes. When you take an Interlude or spend time with someone who cares about you, remove all Solitude Tokens. When you use this Gift without satisfying \nthe Activator, you can ignore the Wound and take 1 Solitude Token instead.","notes":"Yvonne of the Dark - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 26.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"React angrily when the world ignores you or makes it clear to you that no one cares about you."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241694,"modifiedTime":1783973241694,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"Nqv1JMNygLDTc6GC","name":"Dark Ego - Snow Queen","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>Cold and frost have no effect on me are extensions of my soul and I feel \na great affinity for winter. My heart of pure ice delights is easily touched \nwhen I see others suffer.<h3>Dark Ego</h3>The tiny fragment of a magic mirror lies in \nyour right eye, relegating the real you to oblivion. But when tears warm your \neyes, or you hear the word that represents your dominion over the cold, Lady \nStorm comes to her senses and woe to those who stand before her.\nWhile you are Lady Storm, you can lower the Soma cost of Snow Sorceress \nby 1 without creating magical accidents. In addition, you can use Winter’s \nKiss at a distance without spending Soma. If you wish, you can summon a \nsnowstorm that will sweep over your location regardless of previous weather \nconditions. Inside the storm, visibility is reduced to about three feet, and all \ninvolved lower their OL by 1 for each action. While the snowstorm rages, you \ncan use the Gift Winter’s Kiss as a free action once per Exchange. This Gift \nends, and the Hunter becomes Miss Snow once more as soon as you suffer 1 \nWound, or at the end of the Scene.","notes":"Miss Snow and Lady Storm - bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 2.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Cry over something that genuinely moved you. You hear the word \n“Eternity” spoken by someone who is not aware that it will awaken Lady Storm."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241694,"modifiedTime":1783973241694,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"B23jSvAEXlosJlsX","name":"Dark Ego - Shattered Pact","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3><h3>Dark Ego</h3>Those who break the rules must be \npunished. Y ou gain 1 Additional Success on all Position and Defense \nChecks you make against a subject who’s acting in a way that contradicts \nthe statement you recorded using the For the Record effect. If you act \nto harm them, you also inflict 1 Additional Wound. Once per Scene, if \na subject reveals themselves as they really are, as opposed to how they \npreviously presented themselves, or if they break their word, you can \nlecture them on their dishonesty. All your companions gain 1 Additional \nSuccess on their next action.","notes":"Tremoteus Rumpel - bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 4.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Make an argument against the guilty by pointing out their \nmisdeeds."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241694,"modifiedTime":1783973241694,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"7L1GesS0jixSeLjO","name":"Dark Ego - Oknytt’s Legacy","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I have strange powers, and my body is stronger and more resilient \nthan an ordinary child’s. While I’m not ashamed of my \nappearance, these uncanny abilities mark me as different, and I \ntry not to attract attention when I use my power.<h3>Dark Ego</h3>Y ou appeal to your Dark Ego to gain \ngreat powers. If it is day, you must spend 1 Soma. If you have no Soma, \nyou take 1 Wound. If it is night, there is no cost to activate this Gift, as \nyou are a creature of the night. Y ou gain the following powers:\n1. Yellow Eyes: See perfectly in total darkness. Once per Scene, you can \nsee a target for what they really are, unmasking any disguise they may \nbe wearing. \n2. Troll Strength: Once per Scene, you can perform an act of unprecedented strength by lifting or moving a weight equal to ten men. If you \nuse your strength to harm someone, you inflict 1 Additional Wound. \n3. Stone Skin: Once per Scene, you can suffer an attack or hazard while \navoiding any Wounds. Y ou can resist almost everything, including fire, \nfalls, and weapons. Only magic can harm you. Y ou must declare the use \nof this effect before any Defense Check.","notes":"Prince Trollo the Innocent - bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 6.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"You tap into your heritage in front of someone you have helped \nbefore and who is unaware of your true nature."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241694,"modifiedTime":1783973241694,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"BJF50tMsVAwEpeIh","name":"Dark Ego - The Magic of Disbelief","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3><h3>Dark Ego</h3>The Cauldron Fae unleashes \nher magic to enable you to perform amazing actions. As an action, \nyou can formulate a magic sentence including the fragment I don’t \nbelieve and make its effect concrete. For example, “I don’t believe in \ngravity” would allow you to fly, while “I don’t believe the Hunters of \nthe Order exist” would allow you to hurt the Hunters in an attempt to \nmake them disappear. If your statement has no offensive effect, spend \n1 Soma to gain the power you summoned for the entire Scene. On \nthe other hand, if you want the spell to affect a target \nother than yourself, spend 1 Soma \nto inflict a Wound or apply the effect without making a Check. Each \ntime you use the Magic of Disbelief, roll a die. On a roll of 5 or 6, the \nStoryteller gains 1 Prank Token. The Storyteller can spend 1 Prank \nToken during a Scene to activate the effect of this Gift (you do not take a \nWound because the Activator was not normally triggered) and have the \nCauldron Fae cast a spell to complicate your life or attempt to damage \nsomething that represents progress and modernity. If the Storyteller has \nno accumulated Prank Tokens, you may choose to ignore all the Soma \ncosts to activate the effects of this Gift, but the Storyteller will gain 1 \nPrank Token.","notes":"Pietrik and the Cauldron Fae - bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 8.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Without thinking about the possible consequences, throw \nyourself into an action that is impossible for an ordinary person."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241695,"modifiedTime":1783973241695,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"hHeKrgAT3nMr9SKI","name":"Dark Ego - The Great Deception","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3><h3>Dark Ego</h3>The whole world is a lie, and only \nthose who are truly aware of it can pull the strings of any story. During \nthe course of the Scene, you can activate each of the following effects \nonce:\n1. Materialize an item that is useful for the situation you are facing and \nthat an ally of yours is carrying without knowing it.\n2. Switch places with a Minor NPC. The exchange takes place in the \nblink of an eye, and those present will only see where you are now \nand where your target has ended up. Highly skilled NPCs and other \nHunters are immune to this effect.\n3. Make an NPC that you have met before appear in the Scene. This is \nan illusion that will do your bidding and will dissolve as soon as it \ntakes 1 Wound or it becomes clear that it is not the real person.\n4. Gain 1 Additional Success in a Check you make by exploiting a \nsubject’s character flaw.","notes":"Loki the Deceiver - bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 10.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Organize a deception by studying it in detail, or expose a \ndeception to the people being deceived."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241695,"modifiedTime":1783973241695,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"1Lw8FEQq5QLN6KhV","name":"Dark Ego - The Caring Mother","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3><h3>Dark Ego</h3>Choose a female NPC or Hunter \nand name her your Pupil. Y our Pupil must be young and, in your \nopinion, deserving of your benevolence. Y ou will always know where \nyour Pupil is, and she will gain 1 Additional Success to her actions (or \nincrease her OL by 1 in the case of an NPC) if you are present in the \nScene to comfort her with your words. Y ou get 1 Additional Success if \nyou act against someone who endangers your Pupil. If an NPC or Hunter \nuses a Gift to harm your disciple, you can spend 1 Soma to prevent the \nGift from being activated.","notes":"The Silent Mother - bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 12.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Your words inspire a young girl to find her way or protect her \nfrom injustice."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241695,"modifiedTime":1783973241695,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"ZlJ4OGODRKLK9stX","name":"Dark Ego - You Are What You Fight","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>My greatest secret is that I am like those I fight. My true essence is that \nof a Yokai ghost, which is why I have a talent for unearthing Broken \nTales. I try to do good deeds in the hope of reincarnating as a human.<h3>Dark Ego</h3>When you reveal your true nature, \nyour body changes into the form of a humanoid raven. Y ou will gain the \nfollowing abilities:\n1. Y ou can move by flying thanks to the large wings on your back. Y ou gain \n1 Additional Success on all Defense Checks while hovering in the air. \n2. Y ou can use your large beak to strike an enemy as an additional action, \nbut you cannot communicate by speaking.\n3. Y ou gain 1 Additional Success if you act to injure someone who has \ninflicted 1 Wound on you in the current Scene.","notes":"Karasu Kuroi the Wandering Monk - bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 14.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"You reveal your true nature to prove that not all spirits are evil."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241695,"modifiedTime":1783973241695,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"AP515Yyr9I094zXW","name":"Dark Ego - Heigh-ho, Heigh-ho","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>Discipline and order are the keys to victory. We act as a team because \nthat is what has allowed us to survive so far. Team first and foremost.<h3>Dark Ego</h3>If you are preparing for a confrontation, \nno one can stand up to you. If it is on a mission, the Support Team immediately \nre-enters the Scene (even if it means interrupting another task assigned through \nthe On Mission Gift), with all the narrative benefits that can bring. For the rest \nof the Scene, the Main and Support Teams will act as a single Hunter 2 times \nper Exchange, not consecutively. Any personal Gifts from the various members \nmay be used.","notes":"The 7 Hessian Mercenaries - bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 16.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Begin a confrontation or challenge with the singing of your battle \nhymn."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241695,"modifiedTime":1783973241695,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"1C72oBfEyli6ZboQ","name":"Dark Ego - Goddess Blood","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I have a special power over people who are hopelessly attracted to my \npresence. I am shy and often break down when I receive too much \nexplicit attention.<h3>Dark Ego</h3>Y ou have the power of a goddess within you, \neven if you do not know how to use it. When you activate your aura, you \nchoose an NPC who will be kind to you and try to fulfill your every wish. This \nGift will have no effect on someone who has hostile intentions towards you, \nbut you will gain 2 Additional Successes on all Defense Checks you make, \nsince harming you seems an unnatural action even to those who hate you.\nY ou can activate all of the Travel Companion Gift’s effects on Eurylochus at \nthe same time.","notes":"Circe the Alchemist - bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 20.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Unleash your divine power with a charming or swaggering attitude \nat the most inopportune moment."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241695,"modifiedTime":1783973241695,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"hBQCV8Cq9EAADNcc","name":"Dark Ego - Capture the Outlaws","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3><h3>Dark Ego</h3>Under your leadership, evildoers \nare short-lived. Receive 2 Taxes Tokens. At any time during the Scene, \nyou can spend 1 Taxes Token to activate the following additional effects. \nEach effect can only be activated once per Exchange:\n1. Allow one of your allies to act immediately to carry out one of your \norders, even if they have already acted in the Exchange.\n2. Gain 2 Additional Successes for any action you take to stop (not \neliminate) a criminal or prevent his escape.\n3. Reveal an aspect of an NPC’s private business to your advantage, \nsuch as a connection to another NPC or what they are trying to \nprotect at all costs.","notes":"Captain William of Nottingham - bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 22.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Act to capture or render harmless subjects you deem evil."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241695,"modifiedTime":1783973241695,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"L42Q0ELfJhpcqttO","name":"Dark Ego - The Napoleon of Crime","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3><h3>Dark Ego</h3>When you reveal your plan in \nall its glory, the unsuspecting pawns of your game will be left speechless. \nY ou will receive 2 Spider Web Tokens. Y ou can spend them as if they \nwere Soma points. Y ou can also activate the following effects at any time \nin the Scene at a cost of 1 Spider Web Token each:\n1. Discovering the Gift of an NPC. \n2. Allow an ally to activate their Dark Ego by ignoring the Activator. \n3. Provide 1 Additional Success to an Ally’s Position Check.","notes":"Moriarty the Gentleman Thief - Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 2.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Announce your plan loudly. Show everyone that what you \nhave done before has created an advantage in the current situation."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241695,"modifiedTime":1783973241695,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"9Yz8431oFBsj1fMP","name":"Dark Ego - The Vampire","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3><h3>Dark Ego</h3>Self-inflict 1 Wound and release the power of \nthe ancient curse that permeates your body. Y ou gain 1 Additional Success for \neach Position Check you make using your supernatural power. Y ou can use \neach of the following powers once per Scene:\n1. Turn into a cloud of mist. In this form, you will move slowly but can \navoid all obstacles. While in this form, you retain all your senses, can \nonly be injured by magic, and cannot physically interact with objects or \npeople.\n2. Summon three wolves that will act under your total control. The wolves \nare Minor NPCs with the following profiles: \nOL Medium 5 - (1 Wound) - Descriptor: I am a big wild wolf, ready to \nfight to the death for my master. \n3. Communicate telepathically with another person on whom you used one \nof your Gifts during the Scenario.","notes":"The Pale Medic - Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 4.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Drink and savor human blood in front of someone. Alternatively, \nbreak a crucifix or throw away garlic in disgust."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241695,"modifiedTime":1783973241695,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"FToktGKgZT7MwKMY","name":"Dark Ego - Alien Technology","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>Our knowledge is far more advanced than human knowledge, and we \nhave incredible technology at our disposal. We always try to help those \nwho are considered outcasts or excluded from society...<h3>Dark Ego</h3>Y ou can always take advantage of your \nspecial Equipment:\n1. Laser Pistol: An accurate and silent firearm capable of ignoring all \ncommon defenses. Wounds inflicted cannot be healed until the end of the \nScenario. When a target is eliminated, it becomes a pile of ashes and cannot be \nhealed, even with special Gifts.\n2. Fog Generator: Instantly creates a thick black smoke that blocks the \nvisibility of non-aliens. The smoke lasts for a few minutes but can be quickly \ndispersed by a strong wind.\n3. Portable Tripod: A small multifunctional vehicle that moves on three legs \nand can carry up to six passengers. The Tripod can reach up to nine feet in \nheight and can easily avoid obstacles thanks to its flexible legs. \nWhenever you use alien technology and one or more NPCs witness it, you \nget 1 Invasion! Token. At the end of each Scene in which you have used the \nDark Ego, the Storyteller rolls 1 die for each Invasion! Token. If they roll at \nleast one 6, the Invasion! Tokens are reset and your comrades initiate an attack \non Earth. The Storyteller introduces 4 Martian Agents into the Scenario, who, \nif not eliminated by the end of it, will force you to return to the Operations \nCenter, removing you from the current Campaign.\nMartian Agent - OL Medium 5 - (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am an alien skilled in guerrilla warfare. My monstrous appearance \nparalyzes foolish humans with terror. \nAgenda: Eliminate all humans, starting with the most dangerous individuals: \nthe Hunters of the Order.\nGift - Armed for Invasion: A Martian Agent can use a single effect of Alien \nTechnology 1 time per Scene.","notes":"The Respectable Mr. and Mrs. Mars - Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 6.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Show off your alien nature by using strange technology or revealing \nyour true identity."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241695,"modifiedTime":1783973241695,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"6cpBCFdFY18Dwss4","name":"Dark Ego - Reanimator","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>My mad experiments have expanded my knowledge of death and \nthe occult. I can tell the difference between science and magic. I \ngreedily desire anything I deem useful for my research and have no \nqualms about obtaining it.<h3>Dark Ego</h3>Y ou appeal to the power of science to bring \nlife where there is none. Y ou receive 3 Reanimator Tokens. At your touch, \nand by spending 1 Reanimator Token, an inanimate object or corpse will \ncome to life for the duration of the Scene. Decide whether to also spend \n1 Soma to gain control of what you have animated, or to allow this new \ncreature to have free will. The Storyteller will create an NPC profile for \nhumans and animals (including the reanimation of a single part, such as \na hand or leg), or a Threat profile in the case of an inanimate object, such \nas a door or rope. If you are in control, the creation will do whatever you \ntell it to do. If the creation is acting with free will, it will be moved by the \nStoryteller and may even turn against you.","notes":"Doctor V. Frankenstein - Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 8.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Dismember or dig up a corpse, ignoring the horror it may cause \nthose watching."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241695,"modifiedTime":1783973241695,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"h9U9wSSpHFRmZIS0","name":"Dark Ego - Water Fairy","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am an ancient fairy and my magic allows me to manipulate and \ndominate water. I don’t like to be recognized by humans, so I try to \nkeep my powers hidden from prying eyes.<h3>Dark Ego</h3>Y ou can spend 1 Soma to create 2 small pools \nof lake water, three feet wide and five inches deep. The pools will be created \non any surface, and you can create them anywhere within your field of vision. \nWhen you dip your feet into the water, you unleash your thousand-year-old \nfairy powers. Y ou can choose one of these effects as an additional action in \nany Exchange:\n1. Recover 1 Wound you suffered during this Scene.\n2. Move immediately to a place that you can see. No one can stop you, but \nyou must end up with your feet in contact with the water.\n3. Create a dense fog from a water source that limits visibility but has no \neffect on you.\n4. Hit a target with a jet of water from a pool you create. This is a normal \nattack that requires a Position Check and causes 1 Wound.","notes":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 5 - Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 10.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Dive into the water of a lake and drop your disguise, or give advice \nto someone you really care about."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241695,"modifiedTime":1783973241695,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"bttze1pUehxmSCIb","name":"Dark Ego - Taking Destiny into My Own Hands","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3><h3>Dark Ego</h3>Nothing and no one \ncan hold you against your will. Y ou are free from all obstacles and can move \nat any time, even in the midst of battle, without anyone being able to block \nor harm you. By spending 1 Soma, you can automatically break down any \nenvironmental obstacle in your way, such as walls, doors, or a tangled web of \nbrambles. Y our presence undermines the authority of the powerful: all NPCs \ntied to any kind of authority lower their OL by 1; all Hunters tied to faith or \nwith strong leadership skills receive 1 Penalty per Check.","notes":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 6 - Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 12.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Stand up for someone being oppressed, or openly denounce those \nwho hold power over you.\nEquipment: \nA staff sprouting tendrils / A large bar of soap / A sharp razor / A small \npitcher of water / A perfectly polished rock / A light crossbow / A golden \nearring.\nSoma\n 6\nXP\nWounds \n1.\n2.\n3.\nExtra \nWound.\nI am the Princess of Altomonte, and I succeeded my father by taking full control of his lands. I have always rebelled against the old laws \nof the past, which placed all power in the hands of men. The strength of my ideas was unyielding, leading me to carry out serious acts of \nreprisal against the noble families most tied to the old patriarchal traditions. The Order intervened to stop me, but when they realized that \ntaking me prisoner would make me a martyr, I was offered a deal: join the ranks of the Order to fight the darkness. In exchange, I have \nbeen promised favors and political power with which to change the male-dominated society of my era forever."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241695,"modifiedTime":1783973241695,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"O5DYw7Xs9ZUfrCL1","name":"Dark Ego - Infallible Cunning","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>It only takes me a few seconds to assess the situation and use it to \nmy advantage. I have a soft spot for loving families who remind me \nof what I will never have.<h3>Dark Ego</h3>When you activate this Gift, the \nStoryteller will reveal to you the Downside of all NPCs in the Scene. \nY ou’ll also learn the easiest way to escape from your location and the most \nvaluable item present. When a Hunter (including you) performs a Check \nand gets a Standard Outcome, you can spend 1 Soma to add 1 Increment \nof your choice, including a special effect of a Gift possessed by the Hunter \nperforming the action.","notes":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 7 - Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 14.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Take a few minutes to observe the situation and tell the NPC in \nfront of you what you really think of them. \nEquipment: \nA bag of white pebbles / Seven small gold crowns / Valuable coins and \njewels / A mask with the features of an ogre / A pair of valuable traveling \nboots with two hidden stilettos / Contracts and records of secret negotiations \n/ The key to one of your many secret hideouts / A sling. \nSoma\n 6\nXP\nWounds \n1.\n2.\n3.\nExtra \nWound.\nI am the most important criminal of my time, and there are more than a thousand scoundrels in my employ. I have \nsingle-handedly built up my power through cunning, even committing acts that many people consider despicable. \nThose who lecture me on my misdeeds do not understand that the only thing I wanted in my life was a family that loved \nme. The Order disrupted my criminal empire, but when they realized that eliminating me would start a war among \noutlaws across Europe, I was pardoned and welcomed as a Hunter. My gifts and knowledge ensure a constant flow \nof information, which I use to track down whatever the Order is hunting. Locked away in the fortress of my solitude, I \ncontinue to run my empire. Perhaps I can find a true family in the ranks of the Hunters."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241696,"modifiedTime":1783973241696,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"Dkt7QMTpP2KJytIJ","name":"Dark Ego - It’s Time to Kill the Beast","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3><h3>Dark Ego</h3>Once per Scene, if you make an \nattack against an enemy with monstrous characteristics, you automatically \nhit without a Check and your attack inflicts 2 Wounds. All of the Wounds \nyou inflict leave clearly visible marks and cannot be healed by the victim \nuntil the end of the Scenario. When you activate this Gift, the Storyteller will \nreveal to you one Gift of each monstrous opponent in the Scene. \nNote: A “monstrous trait” is defined as any Hunter or NPC with Gifts or \nDescriptors that represent superhuman physical traits and abilities that also \ngive them a monstrous appearance. However, the Storyteller has the final say \non whether or not a Character is monstrous.","notes":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 8 - Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 16.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Openly challenge a monstrous creature by revealing your true nature.\nEquipment: \nThe right weapon for each beast / A cloak that changes color according to \nits surroundings / A small leaf-shaped ocarina / Animal traps / A deer heart \npreserved under spirits / A necklace of wolf fangs. \nSoma\n 6\nXP\nWounds \n1.\n2.\n3.\nExtra \nWound.\nI am a lone beast slayer who has dedicated his entire life to eradicating monsters and aberrations. The \nOne Who Plots in the Shadows corrupted my soul by drawing on the pain of the monsters’ poor victims I \ncould not save. The Order has freed me from this evil influence and welcomed me into its ranks as a strong \narm against all manner of monsters. I do not like to talk or waste time with complicated plans: when it is \ntime to begin the hunt, having my weapons ready is all that matters."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241696,"modifiedTime":1783973241696,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"Uc8oi60EeSLCilRM","name":"Dark Ego - All Eyes on Me","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3><h3>Dark Ego</h3>When you choose to be the center of \nattention, you are the king of the party. Decide what you want to wear and \nwhat valuables you want to display, and you will look the part. Y ou will also \nreceive the following benefits:\n1. All NPCs present will be favorably disposed toward you, and you can \ncreate an Agenda for one of them to represent their strong interest in \nyou. Particularly powerful subjects may require a Position Check, at the \nStoryteller’s discretion. \n2. If a lie is told in your presence, the person who told it suffers 1 Wound \ncaused by bleeding from the eyes.\n3. If you help someone permanently improve the aesthetics of a person or \nplace, you gain 1 Soma. \nThe effect of this Gift lasts until the end of the Scene or until you activate \nanother of your Gifts.","notes":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 9 - Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 18.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Take a few minutes to prepare for a meeting with someone you \ndeem important. \nEquipment: \nThe precious crown that I always wear on my head. \nSoma\n 5\nXP\nWounds \n1.\n2.\n3.\nExtra \nWound.\nI was a vain ruler and had eyes only for beauty. My heart was pure and my desire to help others was \nsincere, but everyone took advantage of me and clouded my vision with false words. Seeing beyond the wall \nof lies cost me dearly, but now I am not afraid. I see everything as it is, even myself. The Order hired me as a \nHunter, asking only that I use my power in the service of justice, without ulterior motives, without falsehood. \nBut is that really the case? I no longer care, for now, the only truth that matters to me is the one I choose to \ncreate with my mind."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241696,"modifiedTime":1783973241696,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
